60 \\cdot (-16) = -10 + 960 = 950, \\\\\n&k = 20, &b = \\frac{160}{20} - 60 \\cdot 20 = 8 - 1200 = -1192, \\\\\n&k = -20, &b = \\frac{160}{-20} - 60 \\cdot (-20) = -8 + 1200 = 1192, \\\\\n&k = 32, &b = \\frac{160}{32} - 60 \\cdot 32 = 5 - 1920 = -1915, \\\\\n&k = -32, &b = \\frac{160}{-32} - 60 \\cdot (-32) = -5 + 1920 = 1915, \\\\\n&k = 40, &b = \\frac{160}{40} - 60 \\cdot 40 = 4 - 2400 = -2396, \\\\\n&k = -40, &b = \\frac{160}{-40} - 60 \\cdot (-40) = -4 + 2400 = 2396, \\\\\n&k = 80, &b = \\frac{160}{80} - 60 \\cdot 80 = 2 - 4800 = -4798, \\\\\n&k = -80, &b = \\frac{160}{-80} - 60 \\cdot (-80) = -2 + 4800 = 4798, \\\\\n&k = 160, &b = \\frac{160}{160} - 60 \\cdot 160 = 1 - 9600 = -9599, \\\\\n&k = -160, &b = \\frac{160}{-160} - 60 \\cdot (-160) = -1 + 9600 = 9599.\n\\end{aligned}\n\\]\n\nThe largest possible value of \\( b \\) is \\( 9599 \\).\n\nThe final answer is \\(\\boxed{9599}\\).",
  "Step 1: We are given the quadratic equation \\( x^2 + bx - 9600 = 0 \\) and need to find how many integer values of \\( b \\) allow for an integer solution that is divisible by both 10 and 12. \n\nStep 2: The least common multiple (LCM) of 10 and 12 is 60. Therefore, we need to find integer solutions \\( x \\) that are multiples of 60 and solve for \\( b \\) in the equation \\( x^2 + bx - 9600 = 0 \\).\n\nStep 3: Let \\( x = 60k \\) where \\( k \\) is an integer. Substituting \\( x = 60k \\) into the quadratic equation, we get:\n\\[\n(60k)^2 + b(60k) - 9600 = 0\n\\]\n\\[\n3600k^2 + 60bk - 9600 = 0\n\\]\n\\[\n60k(60k + b) = 9600\n\\]\n\\[\n60k + b = \\frac{9600}{60k}\n\\]\n\\[\n60k + b = \\frac{160}{k}\n\\]\n\\[\nb = \\frac{160}{k} - 60k\n\\]\n\nStep 4: For \\( b \\) to be an integer, \\( k \\) must be a divisor of 160. We list the divisors of 160:\n\\[\n\\pm 1, \\pm 2, \\pm 4, \\pm 5, \\pm 8, \\pm 10, \\pm 16, \\pm 20, \\pm 32, \\pm 40, \\pm 80, \\pm 160\n\\]\n\nStep 5: We need to find the largest possible \\( b \\). We evaluate \\( b \\) for each divisor \\( k \\):\n- For \\( k = 1 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{1} - 60 \\cdot 1 = 160 - 60 = 100\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = -1 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{-1} - 60 \\cdot -1 = -160 + 60 = -100\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = 2 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{2} - 60 \\cdot 2 = 80 - 120 = -40\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = -2 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{-2} - 60 \\cdot -2 = -80 + 120 = 40\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = 4 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{4} - 60 \\cdot 4 = 40 - 240 = -200\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = -4 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{-4} - 60 \\cdot -4 = -40 + 240 = 200\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = 5 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{5} - 60 \\cdot 5 = 32 - 300 = -268\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = -5 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{-5} - 60 \\cdot -5 = -32 + 300 = 268\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = 8 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{8} - 60 \\cdot 8 = 20 - 480 = -460\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = -8 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{-8} - 60 \\cdot -8 = -20 + 480 = 460\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = 10 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{10} - 60 \\cdot 10 = 16 - 600 = -584\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = -10 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{-10} - 60 \\cdot -10 = -16 + 600 = 584\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = 16 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{16} - 60 \\cdot 16 = 10 - 960 = -950\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = -16 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{-16} - 60 \\cdot -16 = -10 + 960 = 950\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = 20 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{20} - 60 \\cdot 20 = 8 - 1200 = -1192\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = -20 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{-20} - 60 \\cdot -20 = -8 + 1200 = 1192\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = 32 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{32} - 60 \\cdot 32 = 5 - 1920 = -1915\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = -32 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{-32} - 60 \\cdot -32 = -5 + 1920 = 1915\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = 40 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{40} - 60 \\cdot 40 = 4 - 2400 = -2396\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = -40 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{-40} - 60 \\cdot -40 = -4 + 2400 = 2396\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = 80 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{80} - 60 \\cdot 80 = 2 - 4800 = -4798\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = -80 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{-80} - 60 \\cdot -80 = -2 + 4800 = 4798\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = 160 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{160} - 60 \\cdot 160 = 1 - 9600 = -9599\n  \\]\n- For \\( k = -160 \\):\n  \\[\n  b = \\frac{160}{-160} - 60 \\cdot -160 = -1 + 9600 = 9599\n  \\]\n\nStep 6: The largest possible \\( b \\) is 9599.\n\nConclusion:\n\\(\\boxed{9599}\\)",
