  "Step 1: Identify the integer solution that is divisible by both 10 and 12.\nThe least common multiple of 10 and 12 is 60. Therefore, the integer solution must be a multiple of 60. Let the integer solution be \\( x = 60k \\) where \\( k \\) is an integer.\n\nStep 2: Substitute \\( x = 60k \\) into the quadratic equation \\( x^2 + bx - 9600 = 0 \\).\n\\[\n(60k)^2 + b(60k) - 9600 = 0\n\\]\n\\[\n3600k^2 + 60bk - 9600 = 0\n\\]\n\nStep 3: Isolate \\( b \\).\n\\[\n60bk = 9600 - 3600k^2\n\\]\n\\[\nb = \\frac{9600 - 3600k^2}{60k}\n\\]\n\\[\nb = \\frac{9600}{60k} - \\frac{3600k^2}{60k}\n\\]\n\\[\nb = \\frac{160}{k} - 60k\n\\]\n\nStep 4: Determine the integer values of \\( k \\) such that \\( b \\) is an integer.\nFor \\( b \\) to be an integer, \\( \\frac{160}{k} \\) must be an integer. Therefore, \\( k \\) must be a divisor of 160. The divisors of 160 are:\n\\[\n\\pm 1, \\pm 2, \\pm 4, \\pm 5, \\pm 8, \\pm 10, \\pm 16, \\pm 20, \\pm 32, \\pm 40, \\pm 80, \\pm 160\n\\]\n\nStep 5: Calculate \\( b \\) for each divisor of 160 and find the largest possible \\( b \\).\n\\[\n\\begin{aligned}\n&k = 1: &b = \\frac{160}{1} - 60 \\cdot 1 = 160 - 60 = 100 \\\\\n&k = -1: &b = \\frac{160}{-1} - 60 \\cdot (-1) = -160 + 60 = -100 \\\\\n&k = 2: &b = \\frac{160}{2} - 60 \\cdot 2 = 80 - 120 = -40 \\\\\n&k = -2: &b = \\frac{160}{-2} - 60 \\cdot (-2) = -80 + 120 = 40 \\\\\n&k = 4: &b = \\frac{160}{4} - 60 \\cdot 4 = 40 - 240 = -200 \\\\\n&k = -4: &b = \\frac{160}{-4} - 60 \\cdot (-4) = -40 + 240 = 200 \\\\\n&k = 5: &b = \\frac{160}{5} - 60 \\cdot 5 = 32 - 300 = -268 \\\\\n&k = -5: &b = \\frac{160}{-5} - 60 \\cdot (-5) = -32 + 300 = 268 \\\\\n&k = 8: &b = \\frac{160}{8} - 60 \\cdot 8 = 20 - 480 = -460 \\\\\n&k = -8: &b = \\frac{160}{-8} - 60 \\cdot (-8) = -20 + 480 = 460 \\\\\n&k = 10: &b = \\frac{160}{10} - 60 \\cdot 10 = 16 - 600 = -584 \\\\\n&k = -10: &b = \\frac{160}{-10} - 60 \\cdot (-10) = -16 + 600 = 584 \\\\\n&k = 16: &b = \\frac{160}{16} - 60 \\cdot 16 = 10 - 960 = -950 \\\\\n&k = -16: &b = \\frac{160}{-16} - 60 \\cdot (-16) = -10 + 960 = 950 \\\\\n&k = 20: &b = \\frac{160}{20} - 60 \\cdot 20 = 8 - 1200 = -1192 \\\\\n&k = -20: &b = \\frac{160}{-20} - 60 \\cdot (-20) = -8 + 1200 = 1192 \\\\\n&k = 32: &b = \\frac{160}{32} - 60 \\cdot 32 = 5 - 1920 = -1915 \\\\\n&k = -32: &b = \\frac{160}{-32} - 60 \\cdot (-32) = -5 + 1920 = 1915 \\\\\n&k = 40: &b = \\frac{160}{40} - 60 \\cdot 40 = 4 - 2400 = -2396 \\\\\n&k = -40: &b = \\frac{160}{-40} - 60 \\cdot (-40) = -4 + 2400 = 2396 \\\\\n&k = 80: &b = \\frac{160}{80} - 60 \\cdot 80 = 2 - 4800 = -4798 \\\\\n&k = -80: &b = \\frac{160}{-80} - 60 \\cdot (-80) = -2 + 4800 = 4798 \\\\\n&k = 160: &b = \\frac{160}{160} - 60 \\cdot 160 = 1 - 9600 = -9599 \\\\\n&k = -160: &b = \\frac{160}{-160} - 60 \\cdot (-160) = -1 + 9600 = 9599 \\\\\n\\end{aligned}\n\\]\n\nThe largest possible \\( b \\) is \\( 9599 \\).\n\n\\boxed{9599}"
